      "@id": "gist:hasGiver",
      "@type": "owl:ObjectProperty",
      "owl:propertyDisjointWith": {
        "@id": "gist:hasRecipient"
      },
      "rdfs:comment": [
        "NOTE: This property is often used in abstract contexts such as agreements, obligations, contracts, etc., whereas gist:comesFromAgent is intended to describe the physical or electronic transfer of something, such as a package or email, from one agent to another. However, there are contexts in which either may be appropriate, such as the giving of a gift.",
        "DEFINITION: Relates something to the participant that provides it.",
        "EXAMPLE: An offer is made by a giver; an obligation has a giver who is obligated to another person; a gift is presented by the giver."
      ],
      "rdfs:isDefinedBy": {
